criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age ≥18years and ≤80years;

          -  MV time ≤48h;

          -  MV duration is expected to be ≥72h;

          -  The sternocleidomastoid region and pectoralis major region were completely exposed.

          -  Patients or family members are willing to sign informed consent and participate in the
             study.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  There are contraindications to PNS in vitro (Pneumothorax, active tuberculosis,
             pleural adhesions, installation of pacemakers and defibrillators, etc.);

          -  Neuromuscular disease (myasthenia gravis, etc.) or known anatomical abnormalities of
             the diaphragm;

          -  ECMO status;

          -  Hemodynamic instability;

          -  Uncorrected arrhythmias;

          -  Be pregnant;

          -  Clinical end-stage and palliative care patients.
